<p>This privacy policy (this<strong> "Policy"</strong>) describes how Brandish Insights, Inc. and its affiliates and related companies (collectively, <strong>"Brandish Insights"</strong>, <strong>"Company"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>, <strong>"our"</strong>, and<strong> "we"</strong>) collect, use, and share personal information of users of the www.brandishinsights.com website (the "<strong>Site</strong>"), and/or any application, service, functionality, experience, event, or product belonging to, provided by, created by, or operated by Brandish Insights (collectively or individually, the <strong>"Service"</strong>).  </p>

<p><strong>The EU-US Privacy Shield Principles </strong></p>

<p>Brandish Insights is committed to supporting and adhering to the principles and requirements of the EU-US Privacy Shield and is subject to the investigatory and enforcement powers of the Federal Trade Commission (FTC). For further details on the Privacy Shield, please visit: www.privacyshield.gov.</p>

<p>The Privacy Shield Principles describe Company’s accountability for any personal data that Company receives and then transfers to a third party. Should a third-party agent that has been engaged by Company to process personal data on its behalf do so in a manner that is inconsistent with the Privacy Shield Principles, Company may remain responsible and liable thereunder unless Company proves that it is not responsible for the event that led to the damage, the type of data collected, and the purposes for which the data was collected. All individuals must be informed of any third parties to whom their personal data will be transferred, their right to access such data, and the means for limiting the use and disclosure of such data.</p>

<p><strong>WHAT WE COLLECT</strong></p>

<p>We get information about you in a range of ways. </p>

<p><strong>Information You Give Us.</strong> We may collect your‎ name, email address, phone number, username, password, demographic information (such as your gender and occupation) and any other information you may provide directly on our Service.</p>

<p><strong>Information We Get From Others.</strong> We may get information about you from other sources. We may add this to information we get from this Service.</p>

<p><strong>Information Automatically Collected.</strong> We automatically log information about you and your computer and mobile device when you use our Service. For example, when visiting our Service, we may log browser type, browser language, the website you visited before browsing to our Service, pages you viewed, how long you spent on a page, access times and information about your use of and actions on our Service. </p>

<p><strong>Cookies.</strong> We may log information using "Cookies". Cookies are small data files stored on your hard drive by a website. We may use both session Cookies (which expire once you close your web browser) and persistent Cookies (which stay on your computer until you delete them) to provide you with a more personal and interactive experience on our Service. This type of information is collected to make the Service more useful to you and to tailor the experience with us to meet your special interests and needs.</p>

<p><strong>LOCATION INFORMATION</strong></p>

<p>We may use and store information about your location depending on the permissions you have set on your device. We use this information to provide features of our Service, and to improve and customize our Service. You can enable or disable location services when you use our Service at any time, through your mobile device settings.</p>


