<li>with our employees and third party service providers to enable them to provide services such as email delivery, text messaging, customer support, voice messaging, auditing, website hosting, information technology, and other services.</li></ul>

<p>We may also share aggregated and/or anonymized data with others for their own uses.  We may disclose Personal Information as we in our sole discretion deem to be necessary or appropriate: (a) to comply with legal processes or proceedings; (b) under applicable law, which may include laws outside the jurisdiction where you reside and/or conduct your business; (c) to protect the operations of Company; (d) to respond to requests or orders from public and government authorities, which may include public and government authorities outside the jurisdiction where you reside and/or conduct your business; (e) to enforce Company’s Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, or other terms and conditions; (f) to enable Company to pursue remedies or limit the damages or injuries that we may incur, and (g) to protect rights, privacy, safety, or property of you, other Users, Company, or other parties.</p>

<p><strong>SECURITY</strong></p>

<p>Brandish Insights is committed to safeguarding your information. Although we use industry standard security practices and technologies to protect the security of information, it is not possible to guarantee the security of information that is transmitted through the Internet. Company is not responsible for any interception or interruption of any transmissions or communication of information through the Internet, nor is Company responsible for any losses of such information or changes thereto. Each User of our Service is responsible for maintaining the security of any password, user identification, personal identification number (PIN), and any other form of user authentication as may be required or employed in accessing password-protected or secure pages, features, or aspects of the Service. If any breach of security is suspected, Company may suspend or revoke your use of the Service or a portion thereof, without notice so as to protect you and your information until Company completes its investigation. Only authorized users are permitted to access and use secure and password-protected areas, applications, or features of the Service. Any unauthorized access to secure or password-protected features, applications, or areas of the Service is prohibited and be prosecuted criminally. Please notify Brandish Insights immediately if you learn or have reason to suspect that a breach of security has occurred, involving or related to our Service, or if you believe that any interaction with the Service is no longer secure.</p>


<p><strong>INFORMATION CHOICES AND CHANGES</strong></p>

<p>Our marketing emails tell you how to "opt-out." If you opt out, we may still send you non-marketing emails. Non-marketing emails include emails about your accounts and our business dealings with you.</p>

